To run this demo do the following:


- Make sure to have the following set in your xmlBlaster.properties file:

  Protocol.Drivers=......, XML-RPC:org.xmlBlaster.protocol.xmlrpc.XmlRpcDriver, ....
  Protocol.CallbackDrivers=..., XML-RPC:org.xmlBlaster.protocol.xmlrpc.CallbackXmlRpcDriver, ....


- Start xmlBlaster:

  ${JAVA_WRAP} org.xmlBlaster.MainGUI

     or

  ${JAVA_WRAP} org.xmlBlaster.Main


- Start the xml-rpc client from this directory

 java -Dsax.driver=com.sun.xml.parser.Parser javaclients.xmlrpc.XmlRpcHttpClient < demo.xml


Note: There is a helper class in src/java/org/xmlBlaster/client/protocol/xmlrpc
called XmlBlasterProxy.java which clients can use. It wraps the 'low level'
xml-rpc invokation.


enjoy it !

Michele (michele.laghi@attglobal.net)
